http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_rip.gif" align=absmiddle>  Hmmm</span><hr size=1> Did you visit Arch Overseers site? On the front page they describe using(on two different occasions) an SK and a Pali to tank Quarm with the same ch rotation as with their War. So, as to the War still being the prefered tank on big mobs, maybe so for now, but after that spreads around, that will quickly decline to being the case.<br>
<br>
Kunark proved that, as a tank, SK and Pali's sucked. Now, that is no longer the case. You seem to believe that warriors are VASTLY better tanks these days than knights, which simply isn't the case. We are marginally better, and def does make a difference, but not so much on long fights. Presently, for groups anyway, knights are prefered as tanks for groups because they get instant agro when they want. Most groups don't mind that a knight has a few less HPs. Now, if wars were able to taunt at least nearly as well, when the selection is made, the choice is buffs/backup heal/dps/above average tank versus great tank/above average dps. The choice is not so lop sided anymore.<br>
<br>
Do you realize that taunt only succeeds 30% of the time? I have on several occasions, taking 3 or more taunts to regain agro from a slower because taunt failed several times in a row. In that same situation, a knight would have got it first try. When choosing a main tank for a group, and you are a slower or a cleric, who would you pick. But if War had equal taunt, then I am sure that the tank job would be a toss up at that point.<br>
<br>
The same goes for offtank. Suppose you are in a long battle, and slow needs to be recast on the offtank mobs, and you offtanker loses agro. Who do you want trying to get agro back, the war who could fail taunt 3-4 times in a row, and risk getting your slower killed, or the SK/Pali who WILL get agro back. Warriors are not chosen for offtanks. Check any guild.<br>
<br>
Oh, and as for augs you have 19 slots to apply +40 augs (this is providing you do the 437 successful adventures to get enough for every piece 1150pts from Ruj adventures) you can muster up an additional 760 hps. Now, assuming that a knight gets none of these hp augs, and goes for effects only (god, what 19 augs would you get...holy) which do you think improves their individual talents more? 760 hps, or FT15, Vengeance3 x whatever, regen 5 x whatever, +int/+wis aug....etc. Yes, I stand by my statement that augs totally remove the 'sacrafice' of gear for knights.<br>
<br>
No, the least we need is a taunt that is 90% effective (I'll settle for a failure now and then), but at 30% success, I may as well not have taunt. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dwarphwyrrior>Dwarph Wyrrior</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://myimgs.com/data/dwarph/dwarf_lord_pencil10x10.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/12/03 5:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2113.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://myimgs.com/data/dwarph/dwarf_lord_pencil60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_rip.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Hmmm</span><hr size=1> Even if no one else agrees, i HAVE to say that SKs and Pallys MAY have been really gimp before Luclin, but lately, they can get within 500hp of warriors at high end, when equally equiped. And the time gear has all of mana, hp, and focus effects making another part of the argument obsolete. <br>
