If they are supposed to be 75% tank and 25% caster - then take 25% of there HP and AC away and give em whatever they need to be casters. Give them some spells that arent as aggro. the problem isnt the warriors - its the hybrids. Maybe if they arent such a good trade in the  Heal mana/ Ability to hold aggro equation then warriors will again be more sought after for their ability to mitigate the mobs DPS at a more efficient heal mana rate. Just please don't let anyone screw up our class like they did the hybrid classes - two wrongs don't make a right. <br>
<br>
The point isn't so much that warriors are unbalanced as it is that Paladins and SK's are over balanced. in a half and half deal they got the big half, and yet i wouldnt trade being a warrior for any class in Norrath. Please be very carefull about what is asked, cause the one sure thing that can ruin this game is to make it too easy. Think back to the edge of your seat thrill of making the run from FV to LOiO before they tamed the spiders. they have taken out alot of the game's challenge along the way due to the pissing and moaning masses complaints. I suppose thats my opinion and i will no doubt be slapped silly for voicing it.<br>
BTW - we do have alot of good things going for us in the aa dept., but the general concensus seems to be that you should get levels first then aa. all this does is propogate the theory that pallys and sk's are better than us - no we dont get lifetaps and heals, but the damage mitigation and agility bonus' are worth ALOT of HP. think about it, get missed twice on a mob thats hitting for 400 and you just gained 800 HP, mitigate a 400 hit down to 80 ( quite normal) and there is another 320 HP. <br>
<br>
I have just reassured myself that my path is true and that i will not move to 56 before i have my ND3, CS3 and CA3. i want to be the best warrior i can be and these are my responsibility.<br>
