<br>
they nerfed the spiders?? you're right there are too many crybabies on the boards and the design team is listening to them.<br>
<br>
ok getting back on topic. some say that palladins take more damage than warriors. thats debatable because of the also mentioned problem that slow cannot usually be cast on a mob till it is down by 10 or 15 percent health. you think 10 or 15 isnt much? that first 10 percent takes a LONG time to do because nobody is nuking and its the nukes that do the most damage. that first 10 percent can be a third of the fight and the mob does more damage on that third than on the rest of the fight combined. and all those hitpoints the warrior supposedly has get eaten very quickly during that no-slow time.<br>
<br>
most of the complaints here revolve around experience groups not raid bosses so ill skip the objections about 2000hp lifetaps. in experience groups the damage mitigation of armor class does help and the defensive skill reactivated on first pull after it refreshes can mitigate at least 15 percent of total melee damage on a typical exp run (at level 60). compound that with the 12 percent hitpoint difference of warrior and we are up to just over 25 percent. but now a warrior has to deal with an unslowed mob twice as long as a palidin increasing melee damage taken by about one third. warriors also take more riposte damage. it follows that warriors are harder to keep alive with complete heal than palladins and it gets much worse for non-complete heals and regen buffs.<br>
<br>
so paladins seem to win on the &quot;healability index&quot;. <br>
<br>
paladins win on the &quot;save the caster index&quot; no contest.<br>
<br>
warriors win on melee damage dealt but lets face it neither class does much damage so who really cares?<br>
<br>
so far the paladin is ahead.<br>
<br>
paladins have manna and the manna they have can be converted to manna of other casters. the manna they spare the cleric by taking over pacify duty in crowded ldon dungeons is absolutely enormous. and they can do pacify work even if they are main tank if they have manna buffs. this last point doesnt affect the decision of who to have MT when both a pally and warrior are in the same group. but it does directly affect which class you would want to recruit.<br>
<br>
